@mavericklam still not entirely clear which case youre talking about. 

if it is chaincode A installed on peer A and chaincode A installed on peer B then yes, the state db is a reflection of the same ledger.

if it is an instance of chaincode A and and an instance of chaincode B they do not share the same state, but they can get information about each other's state by querying and sending invokes between them if and only if they are instantiated on the same channel

