[ ](https://chat.hyperledger.org/channel/fabric-chaincode-dev?msg=cwzatah7jR9w9Hojv) @mcoblenz - yes you can define multiple Smart Contracts into one chaincode package.  All the functions in all Smart Contracts will be callable/accessible by name - unless there are duplicate names.  In the event of duplicate function names, the one from the first contract will become the default and will be used. (I think 'first' is determined alphabetically.)
But rather than rely on defaults, best practise is to namespace each contract as per the Commercial Paper Sample:
```
constructor() {
    super('org.papernet.commercialpaper');
}
```

